major league baseball through the lens events at stanford major league baseball through the lens facebook twitter email print add to calendar america's favorite pastime is one of the most photographed sports in the world and images of our favorite teams and players highlight sports pages websites smart phones and baseball cards while the baseball experience for the average fan is one of relaxing afternoons eating hot dogs and enjoying the big league atmosphere to the professional sports photographer baseball is a test of concentration deadlines and handeye coordination join us tonight to hear what it takes to get the picture from three of the best photographers on the baseball beat major league baseball and sports illustrated photographer brad mangin san jose mercury news staff photographer nhat meyer and the san francisco giants photographer andy kuno will share their images and stories about how they captured and approached the 2010 giants championship season the program will be hosted by john todd a professional photographer who operates international sports images the official photography supplier to the us men and women's soccer teams stanford athletics uc berkeley and the women's professional soccer league thursday september 29 7 00 pm annenberg auditorium cummings art building free no registration is required when thursday september 29 2011 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where annenberg auditorium cummings art building map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading visual arts sponsor continuing studies contact 725 2650 continuingstudies stanford edu admission free no registration is required permalink http events stanford edu events 286 28637 more info last modified september 26 2011
